	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N Orls</placeName> <date>Apl. 16. 5610</date>.</p>
				<p>My dear friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your few lines <date>7th</date> inst<lb/> just to hand.  In reply I state that<lb/> until now I could not decide upon<lb/> a day for the consecration&#44; as I have<lb/> had great trouble in getting up a chair<lb/> for the occasion.  Every body takes it<lb/> very easy excepting myself&#44; as the<lb/> board of officers have <hi rend="underline">very kindly</hi> left<lb/> everything to me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Now I expect <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName> here<lb/> by the <date>3d.</date> proximo and I will have<lb/> everything ready by that time&#8212;<lb/> I propose to consecrate the building<lb/> say 2 or 3 days before <hi rend="underline">Shebnate</hi><add>&#63;</add>&#44; say<lb/> on the <date>13th</date> or <date>14th of May</date>&#8212;so you<lb/> ought to be here at latest by the <date>12th.</date><lb/> and if you could be here a few days<lb/> earlier I would prefer it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have recd. Bill Ladg for the<lb/> box of Candles from <persName>Uncle Theodore</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This consecration takes up all<lb/> my time&#44; first to arrange&#44; and<lb/> then to carry out my plans.  This<lb/> week I got the pamphlets printed<lb/> with the order of the consecration.<lb/>  I am much worried as to the manner<lb/> of disposing the tickets&#44; I know however</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><add>&#63;</add> I shall strive to please all<lb/> I shall nevertheless receive more<lb/> curses than blessings&#44; but I am<lb/> getting used to this&#44; and so long as<lb/> I feel that I do my duty for the<lb/> credit of the <hi rend="underline">nation</hi>&#44; I care<lb/> not for the opinions of others.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Alas I wish it was all over<lb/> for I am kept in one constant<lb/> state of excitement despite my<lb/> material coolness.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Let me say in conclusion<lb/> that when you arrive here there<lb/> is always a plate at my table<lb/> from which you may partake in<lb/> safety.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As to your affairs with your<lb/> congregation I freely <sic>sympathise</sic><lb/> with you.  I understand fully from<lb/> sad experience&#44; what contending<lb/> emotions you must have<lb/> between duty and dignity.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Excuse my haste and</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">believe me yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">ever truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Gershom K</persName></p>
				<p>I gave <persName>Mr Nathan&#39;s</persName> gown to <persName>Barney<add>&#63;</add> B Hart</persName><lb/> a long time ago.  He sent it in the steam<lb/> ship Falcon I believe to some one he</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>does business with requesting<lb/> it to be immediately <sic>forwded</sic><lb/> to you.  Bring it with you or<lb/> send it as quickly as possible<lb/> <persName>Nathan</persName> will feel very awkward<lb/> not to have his gown.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">yours again faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">GK</persName></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Penna.</placeName></p>
		</body>
